<br>
I'm at a level where I can make ornate chainmail.  Ornate chainmail is the upgrade to banded armor for chain wearing classes (rangers, bards, rogues and shaman).  It has higher AC and lower weight than banded.<br>
<br>
A comparison follows (unk means unknown, weight shown as sm-med-large, prices are market prices):<br>
<br>
<br>
Head<br>
   Banded:  Helm: AC 8, wt 3.4-4.5-5.6 - 8PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Coif: AC 9, unk-4.0-unk - 50PP<br>
Face<br>
   Banded:  Mask: AC 4, wt 0.8-1.0-1.3 - 4PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Veil:  AC 5, wt unk-0.5-unk - 50PP<br>
Neck<br>
   Banded:  Gorget: AC 5, wt 1.5-2.0-2.5 - 5PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Gorget:  AC 6, wt unk-1.5-unk - 25PP<br>
Shoulders<br>
   Banded:  Mantle: AC 6, wt 2.6-3.5-4.4 - 6PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Mantle:  AC 7, wt unk-3.0-unk - 50PP <br>
Arms<br>
   Banded:  Sleeves: AC 7, wt 2.6-3.5-4.4 - 7PP <br>
   Ornate Chain:  Sleeves:  AC 8, wt unk-3.0-unk - 50PP<br>
Wrist<br>
   Banded:  Bracers: AC 6, wt 1.5-2.0-2.5 - 6PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Bracelet: AC 7, wt unk-1.5-unk - 25PP<br>
Hands<br>
   Banded:  Gauntlets: AC 7, wt 3.0-4.0-5.0 - 7PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Gloves:  AC 8, wt unk-3.5-unk - 50PP<br>
Chest<br>
   Banded:  Mail: AC 15, wt 5.6-7.5-9.4 - 15PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Tunic:  AC 16, wt unk-7.0-unk - 75PP<br>
Back<br>
   Banded:  Cloak: AC 7, wt 3.0-4.0-5.0 - 7PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Cloak: AC 8, wt unk-3.5-unk - 50PP<br>
Waist<br>
   Banded:  Belt: AC 6, wt 1.9-2.5-3.1 - 6PP<br>
   Ornate Chain:  Skirt: AC 7, wt unk-2.0-unk - 50PP<br>
Legs<br>
   Banded:  Leggings: AC 8, wt 4.1-5.5-6.9 - 8PP<br>
   Ornate Chain: Leggings: AC 9, wt unk-5.0-unk - 75PP<br>
Feet<br>
   Banded:  Boots:  AC 6, wt 3.8-5.0-6.3 - 6PP<br>
   Ornate CHain:  Boots:  AC 7, wt unk-4.5-unk - 25PP<br>
<br>
As you can see, you basically save 0.5 wt per piece of ornate chain and get one AC point increase over banded.  Full ornate chain would therefore weigh 6.5 less than full banded and provide 13 additional AC points.<br>
<br>
Note for all you plate classes out there (Ya!  You, they guy wearing bronze!).  Most ornate chain pieces have the same AC as bronze (except for helm, gauntlets, breastplate, greaves and boots which are 1 AC better) BUT they have almost 25-50% of the weight of the bronze.  Fine Plate armor is just around the corner - but this is selling for about 80-240PP per piece (depends on the number of medium quality sheets needed)<br>
<br>
The pricing is reflected on a per HQ Ring basis (which seems to be how the market is currently stabilizing).  Ever pattern requires a number of HQ rings - HQ rings are made on a forge with a Large Block of HQ Ore (which is made from three small blocks of HQ ore).  The ore is drop only and comes off of goblins in SolA, HHK and Permafrost.  The common ore drop is a small block of HQ ore.<br>
<br>
The recipe for Ornate Chain is chainmail pattern, smithy hammer, silver bar, water and HQ ring(s).  If someone needs the armor and is willing to cover material costs and help me gather ore, I'll be more than willing to help them do it.  Note, not all pieces are trivial to me yet so we may have some fizzles.<br>
